![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f0684443-1971-4296-bec3-f35cac9fe873/214.jpg?format=original)

It's been almost 10 years since Warner Bros and DC Comics decided to get in on the shared cinematic universe game. Starting with Man of Steel, the DCEU as we knew it was born and sought to mimic the MCU in both quality and success. Unfortunately, the world originally created for DC by Zack Snyder seems to be coming to an end with rumors of The Flash movie rewriting the future of the DCEU. Before that happens, let us look back at the 11 films to come out under that banner, and see where the whole thing went wrong!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
